x}- rac{\pi}{3}{/tex} b. {tex}- rac{2 \pi}{3}{/tex} c. {tex} rac{\pi}{3}{/tex} d. {tex} rac{2 \pi}{3}{/tex} 1 2. If {tex}{A}=\left[{a}_{{ij}}ight]{/tex} is a {tex}3 	imes 3{/tex} diagonal matrix such that {tex}{a}_{11}=1, {a}_{22}=5{/tex} and {tex}{a}_{33}=-2{/tex} , then {tex}|{A}|{/tex} is: a. 0 b. -10 c. 10 d. 1 1 3. If {tex}A=k B{/tex} , where {tex}A{/tex} and {tex}B{/tex} are two square matrices of order {tex}n{/tex} and {tex}k{/tex} is a scalar, then: a. {tex}|{A}|={k}|{B}|{/tex} b. {tex}|{A}|={k}^{{n}}|{B}|{/tex} c. {tex}|{A}|={k}+|{B}|{/tex} d. {tex}|{A}|=|{B}|^{{k}}{/tex} 1 3. If {tex}f(x)=\left\{ egin{array}{cc} rac{\sin ^{2} a x}{x^{2}}, & x 
