 y \geq 0{/tex} 3 SECTION-D This section comprises 4 Long Answer (LA) type questions of 5 marks each. 32. In a rough sketch, mark the region bounded by {tex}y=1+|x+1|, x=-2{/tex} , {tex}{x}=2{/tex} and {tex}{y}=0{/tex} . Using integration, find the area of the marked region. 5 33. Three students run on a racing track such that their speeds add up to {tex}6 {~km} / {h}{/tex} . However, double the speed of the third runner added to the speed of the first results in {tex}7 {~km} / {h}{/tex} . If thrice the speed of the first runner is added to the original speeds of the other two, the result is {tex}12 {~km} / {h}{/tex} . Using matrix method, find the original speed of each runner. 5 34. (i) For a positive constant 'a', differentiate {tex}{a}^{{t}+ rac{1}{{t}}}{/tex} with respect to {tex}\left({t}+ rac{1}{{t}}ight)^{{a}}{/tex} , where t is a non-zero real number. 5 OR (ii) Find {tex} rac{d y}{d x}{/tex} if {tex}y^{x}+x^{y}+x^{x}=a^{b}{/tex} , where {tex}a{/tex} and {tex}b{/tex} are constants. 5 35. (i) Find the foot of the perpendicular drawn from the point {tex}(1,1,4){/tex} on the line {tex} rac{{x}+2}{5}= rac{{y}+1}{2}= rac{-{z}+4}{-3}{/tex} . 5 OR (ii) Find the point on the line {tex} rac{{x}-1}{3}= rac{{y}+1}{2}= rac{{z}-4}{3}{/tex} at a distance of {tex}2 \sqrt{2}{/tex} units from the point ( {tex}-1,-1,2{/tex} ). 5 SECTION-E This section comprises 3 case study-based questions of 4 marks each Case Study - 1 36. Let {tex}A{/tex} be the set of 30 students of class XII in a school. Let {tex}f: A ightarrow N, N{/tex} is a set of natural numbers such that function {tex}{f}({x})={/tex} Roll Number of student x. On the basis of the given information, answer the following: Is f a bijective function? (1) Give reasons to support your answer to (i). (1) Let R be a relation defined by the teacher to plan the seating arrangement of students in pairs, where {tex}{R}=\{({x}, {y}): {x}, {y}{/tex} are Roll Numbers of students such that {tex}{y}=3 {x}\}{/tex} . List the elements of R . Is the relation R reflexive, symmetric and transitive? Justify your answer. (2) OR Let R be a relation defined by {tex}{R}=\left\{({x}, {y}): {x}, {y}ight.{/tex} are Roll Numbers of students such that {tex}\left.{y}={x}^{3}ight\}{/tex} . List the elements of R . Is R a function ? Justify your answer. (2) 4 Case Study - 2 37. A gardener wanted to plant vegetables in his garden. Hence he bought 10 seeds of brinjal plant, 12 seeds of cabbage plant and 8 seeds of radish plant. The shopkeeper assured him of germination probabilities of brinjal, cabbage and radish to be {tex}25 \%, 35 \%{/tex} and {tex}40 \%{/tex} respectively. But before he could plant the seeds, they got mixed up in the bag and he had to sow them randomly. Based upon the above information, answer the following questions: Calculate the probability of a randomly chosen seed to germinate. (2) What is the probability that it is a cabbage seed, given that the chosen seed germinates? (2) 4 Case Study - 3 38. A carpenter needs to make a wooden cuboidal box, closed from all sides, which has a square base and fixed volume. Since he is short of the paint required to paint the box on completion, he wants the surface area to be minimum. On the basis of the above information, answer the following questions : Taking length = breadth = x m and height = y m, express the surface area (S) of the box in terms of x and its volume (V), which is constant. (1) Find {tex} rac{{dS}}{{dx}}{/tex} . (1) Find a relation between x and y such that the surface area (S) is minimum. (2) OR If surface area (S) is constant, the volume (V) {tex}= rac{1}{4}\left({Sx}-2 {x}^{3}ight){/tex} , x being the edge of base. Show that volume ( V ) is maximum for {tex}{x}=\sqrt{ rac{{S}}{6}}{/tex} . (2) 4

